{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:43:58.737Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Ticket Data Model**\n\nI'm now focusing on the ticket data model. I've decided to incorporate status filters and refine the ticket creation process to be frontend-only, adding tickets locally in the browser. I'm also settling on specific categories: Project Delivery, AI Operations, Billing, Documents, Access, Governance, and General. I'm aiming for a calm, secure, operational UI, and mobile-first design. I've also checked the lint and build processes. I've examined the `SupportTicket` interface to consider how to add category and linkedProject. I may use `EnrichedSupportTicket`.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:43:59.941Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Mapping Ticket Enrichment Data**\n\nI'm now enriching the initial ticket data. I've taken the existing `previewSupportTickets` array and mapped new tickets to it, assigning default categories and projects dynamically. I've made specific assignments for a few tickets, ensuring categories like \"AI Operations,\" \"Project Delivery,\" and \"Governance\" are linked to projects such as \"Sovereign Core Sandbox 02\" and \"Federal Ledger Enclave Alpha\". I'm using `useState` to manage the enriched ticket array.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:44:01.705Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing the Layout**\n\nI'm now designing the support center layout, starting with a striking Hero section that will feature either \"CLIENT SUPPORT RADAR\" or \"SECURE OPERATIONS BRIDGE,\" along with a visual of a secure terminal connection and interactive stats counters. I'm planning a 2-column layout for larger screens, with the form and listing sections, stacking responsively on mobile. The form will feature a \"NEW DIRECT SECURE WIRE\" theme, with intuitive inputs for subject, category, priority, and linked project, and a detailed telemetry description. The listing section will include a filter bar.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:44:03.857Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Drafting the Support Center Layout**\n\nI'm now focusing on the ticket list and detailed view. I plan a polished grid, showing Ticket ID, title, priority, status, category, and creation time. Selecting a ticket will show its details, with parameters and a \"Secured Reply Thread.\" The interactive reply box lets users enter text and \"Transmit Reply,\" adding a new reply to the ticket's replies array in local state. This should provide a truly interactive and modern user experience.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:44:05.391Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Aesthetic Design**\n\nI'm now refining the visual aesthetic. I've chosen a deep black background (`#030303`) with subtle dark slate elements and minimal white borders. I'm focusing on sleek typography, large mono elements, and clear hierarchy, utilizing glow effects and glowing indicators. I'm aiming for a premium, non-generic look, avoiding SaaS card or nested boxes in favor of a clean, secure feel.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
